rows.label: tev078601_SEL1011
rows.name: Ask Shiraton about humans.

rows.label: tev078601_SEL1021
rows.name: Ask Shiraton about recent developments.

rows.label: tev078601_SEL2021
rows.name: Ask Shiraton about recent developments.

rows.label: tev078601_SEL3021
rows.name: Ask Shiraton about recent developments.

rows.label: tev078601_MSG1001
rows.name:
Humans often seem to fight amongst themselves
and commit various crimes here in the city.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG1002
rows.name:
I heard that humans who were found likely to harm
others were not allowed onto your "White Whale"
ship. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG1003
rows.name:
But Tracey said that the worst humans tended to be the
craftiest at evading such precautions. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG1004
rows.name:
Hmm. My kind merely exist to perform our function.
You humans, on the other hand, seem to be a much
less straightforward people. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG1009
rows.name:
I had hoped to continue dealing regularly with
Roselle, but it seems she has been arrested. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG1010
rows.name:
So I had to put more effort into my recovery work.
I now visit the residential and commercial districts,
and anywhere else voltant can be found. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG1011
rows.name:
The humans whose voltant I devoltanize always seem
quite pleased to have me. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG1012
rows.name:
After being treated with disgust wherever my people
have gone, it is quite gratifying to feel that we are
needed here. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG2001
rows.name:
Outside of the rare occasions like this when I leave the
city, I spend my days devoltanizing the voltant that
Roselle brings to me. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG2002
rows.name:
I do not fully understand her oft-stated assertion that
we are "business partners." *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG2003
rows.name:
But in a city the size of New LA, there would certainly
be a limit to how much voltant we would be able to
locate by ourselves. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG2004
rows.name:
So it is certainly true that Roselle's "business" has been
a lifesaver for us. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG3001
rows.name:
Until recently, humans were typically alarmed when
they ran into us at night, and often reported our
presence to the authorities. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG3002
rows.name:
And when we'd enter a shop, we'd be asked to leave
immediately, lest we contaminate the products.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG3003
rows.name:
It was quite a difficult life here in New LA. *fsssh*
But Tracey has been explaining to people that we
Zaruboggan are not dangerous.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG3004
rows.name:
She has even threatened to arrest humans who persist
in discriminatory behavior. *fsssh* As a result,
the humans have come to understand us better.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev078601_MSG3005
rows.name:
It has made life in New LA more pleasant for us.
Dealing with Tracey has not always been so easy,
but she has our gratitude now. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]
